1
00:00:23,839 --> 00:00:27,800
Master, Jiao Lijun claimed
he was wronged yesterday.

2
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:29,679
And now today he surrenders.

3
00:00:30,699 --> 00:00:31,920
This is so abnormal.

4
00:00:32,359 --> 00:00:36,000
None of the suspects
in the 6.10 case were normal.

5
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,539
One more won't hurt.

6
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:41,520
Let's see what tricks he can pull.

7
00:00:43,380 --> 00:00:45,399
You were the last person
to see Jiao Lijun.

8
00:00:46,259 --> 00:00:47,240
Any leads?

9
00:00:48,579 --> 00:00:51,340
I've always suspected Jiao Lijun
is Meng Xiaoliang's father.

10
00:00:52,619 --> 00:00:55,079
I even tested Meng Guangcai
on that, remember?

11
00:00:56,259 --> 00:01:00,859
You're saying Jiao Lijun surrendered
because he felt he couldn't escape?

12
00:01:01,079 --> 00:01:02,759
After dealing with them for many years,

13
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:05,299
my experience tells me Jiao Lijun

14
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:08,959
is the most meticulous of the group.

15
00:01:08,959 --> 00:01:11,780
He probably figured out we're
looking for Meng Xiaoliang's father.

16
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:16,799
So it seems your suspicion was right.

17
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:18,579
Hard to say.

18
00:02:29,824 --> 00:02:33,549
=The Silent Rift=

19
00:02:33,549 --> 00:02:36,053
=Episode 9=
(The Fourth Person)

20
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:52,879
Why?

21
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:58,180
I often ask myself that question.

22
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:01,379
For brotherhood?

23
00:03:03,039 --> 00:03:03,960
For money?

24
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:07,259
Or was it my own choice?

25
00:03:09,099 --> 00:03:14,099
The worst thing in life is making
the wrong choice at a critical moment.

26
00:03:15,099 --> 00:03:18,159
Get it wrong, and you'll pay for it
the rest of your life.

27
00:03:20,099 --> 00:03:21,960
If I had been braver back then.

28
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:27,099
If I had been in the right place
at the right time.

29
00:03:27,099 --> 00:03:29,500
Then maybe everything
would be different now.

30
00:03:31,319 --> 00:03:32,740
But wrong is wrong.

31
00:03:35,539 --> 00:03:37,319
What I missed wasn't the opportunity,

32
00:03:41,379 --> 00:03:43,740
it was my countless hesitations.

33
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:50,099
But the world is fair.

34
00:03:51,379 --> 00:03:52,520
It always makes you

35
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:55,599
trade what you have for what you want.

36
00:03:56,740 --> 00:03:58,259
I had nothing to begin with.

37
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:00,539
Now, it's like one click
back to factory settings.

38
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:03,520
Are you talking about the 6.10 case?

39
00:04:06,599 --> 00:04:07,460
I surrender.

40
00:04:09,379 --> 00:04:11,240
Caisheng Group isn't just us three.

41
00:04:12,180 --> 00:04:14,960
So many people poured their hearts
into building what it is today.

42
00:04:15,659 --> 00:04:17,600
I can't accept that my mistakes

43
00:04:17,959 --> 00:04:20,740
have plunged the group
into such a huge crisis.

44
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:23,740
I also can't accept
that because of me, an innocent person

45
00:04:26,819 --> 00:04:28,100
has been wrongfully accused.

46
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:29,819
So you're saying

47
00:04:30,819 --> 00:04:33,699
in the 6.10 case,
you were one of the robbers?

48
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:35,759
Yes.

49
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:38,259
I took part in the robbery.

50
00:04:39,259 --> 00:04:43,139
So I know Meng Guangcai
is completely innocent in all this.

51
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,540
Alright, tell us about it.

52
00:04:49,253 --> 00:04:52,133
(1993, Beiyan County,
Shaliang Rural Credit Union)

53
00:04:54,879 --> 00:04:55,500
Behave!

54
00:04:56,939 --> 00:04:58,439
Get down!

55
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:02,939
Get back!

56
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,639
Over ten years ago.

57
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:23,639
You remember it clearly.

58
00:05:25,879 --> 00:05:30,699
When something like this happens,
you never forget it.

59
00:05:30,879 --> 00:05:34,220
Tell me, who were
the robbers at the scene?

60
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,699
There were three people.

61
00:05:42,660 --> 00:05:44,639
(Me, Zuo Long,)

62
00:05:45,699 --> 00:05:47,104
(and another named Ma Zhongwu,)

63
00:05:47,104 --> 00:05:48,384
but I wasn't familiar with him.

64
00:05:48,384 --> 00:05:49,040
Okay.

65
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,379
Zuo Long, Ma Zhongwu.

66
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,379
What about Wang Dazhu?

67
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:55,000
I

68
00:05:55,220 --> 00:05:56,639
don't understand what you mean.

69
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:59,660
You wouldn't forget
something like that, would you?

70
00:06:08,339 --> 00:06:09,040
Yes.

71
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,420
Wang Dazhu was there.

72
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,819
We were four in total.

73
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:26,160
Four people.

74
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,699
Who shot at the scene?

75
00:06:43,879 --> 00:06:45,839
I've already confessed.

76
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:47,639
What's there to ask?

77
00:06:47,639 --> 00:06:49,540
What more do I have to say?

78
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:50,759
Wang Dazhu.

79
00:06:51,439 --> 00:06:53,699
Who else was with you
on the robbery day?

80
00:06:59,540 --> 00:07:02,540
I've said it at least eighty times,
if not a hundred.

81
00:07:03,379 --> 00:07:06,040
Zuo Long and Ma Zhongwu
were the principals.

82
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,000
I was the accessory.

83
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,259
If that's not enough, I'll say it
a hundred more times. All right?

84
00:07:11,420 --> 00:07:14,560
I advise you to give up the fantasy.

85
00:07:15,379 --> 00:07:17,420
We have solid testimonies.

86
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:20,639
You weren't three that day. It was four!

87
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,040
Still acting, Meng Guangcai?

88
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:27,000
Jiao Lijun has surrendered.

89
00:07:28,819 --> 00:07:29,779
Jiao Lijun?

90
00:07:30,319 --> 00:07:32,879
Jiao Lijun has admitted
to all his crimes.

91
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:35,319
He was the fourth person there.

92
00:07:38,639 --> 00:07:40,560
You've all confused me.

93
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,759
How did a fourth person come up now?

94
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:47,560
Anything else to say?

95
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,980
Still insisting on your innocence,

96
00:07:51,319 --> 00:07:54,439
or that you never
took part in the robbery?

97
00:07:54,939 --> 00:07:56,920
Of course, I wasn't
involved in the robbery.

98
00:07:58,220 --> 00:08:01,100
I knew nothing
about their activities either.

99
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:06,879
Your buddies have admitted
to taking part in the robbery.

100
00:08:07,819 --> 00:08:10,720
So you, the big brother, had nothing
to do with the 6.10 case, right?

101
00:08:18,220 --> 00:08:19,560
Let me say it again.

102
00:08:21,139 --> 00:08:23,759
I'm a law-abiding businessman.
I didn't involve in the robbery.

103
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:27,500
All this about Wang Dazhu
and Jiao Lijun being in on the robbery,

104
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,779
and even my son
not being my flesh and blood,

105
00:08:30,819 --> 00:08:32,639
I don't believe any of it.

106
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:34,759
I'll also say this again.

107
00:08:35,259 --> 00:08:38,659
I strongly suspect this
is Zhu Helai's psychological tactic

108
00:08:38,940 --> 00:08:40,700
to frame me and force my hand.

109
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:47,039
I really feel bad for your buddies.

110
00:08:48,019 --> 00:08:50,399
The big brother they followed
with all their hearts

111
00:08:51,519 --> 00:08:55,279
turns out to be such a coward
who'll do anything to save himself.

112
00:08:59,365 --> 00:09:00,639
(2006, Villa in Beiyan Outskirts)

113
00:09:00,639 --> 00:09:02,460
Before the police come knocking,

114
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:06,779
we need to figure out what to do next.

115
00:09:08,779 --> 00:09:11,100
Zuo Long is the principal.

116
00:09:12,639 --> 00:09:14,700
Ma Zhongwu is the accessory.

117
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:18,399
Once you confirm they're really
investigating the credit union case,

118
00:09:18,779 --> 00:09:19,960
don't think.

119
00:09:20,340 --> 00:09:21,899
Just name these two.

120
00:09:22,519 --> 00:09:25,019
This is our code.

121
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:28,759
Two people really did go missing,

122
00:09:29,399 --> 00:09:30,500
both locals.

123
00:09:30,899 --> 00:09:31,899
One is Zuo Long.

124
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:34,039
Another is Ma Zhongwu.

125
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,700
Have you seen this person?

126
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,080
Isn't this Zuo Long?

127
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:38,600
Are you Ma Zhongwu's mother?

128
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:42,320
If those outside notice the police
are looking for these two,

129
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,879
that counts as receiving the signal,

130
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,899
and we can move to the next step.

131
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:49,460
Dazhu, tell me, for someone alive,

132
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:52,600
what's the most obvious thing he does?

133
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,500
It's money!

134
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,159
People need money to live.

135
00:09:57,279 --> 00:09:59,379
Ma Zhongwu and Zuo Long,

136
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:02,000
around 2006,

137
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:05,100
suddenly started sending money home
as if they planned it.

138
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:09,720
Those whose fate is unknown,
we can make them alive again.

139
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,500
Those who are a headache,
we can make them dead.

140
00:10:14,379 --> 00:10:18,379
We need the whole village to know
Huang Mantang died far from home.

141
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:22,500
Lijun, you're the only one
I trust to handle this.

142
00:10:23,259 --> 00:10:26,019
(Cemetery Registration Form)
You signed Huang Mantang's cemetery form.

143
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,460
You also paid for the burial expenses.

144
00:10:28,879 --> 00:10:30,200
And you said you had no contact?

145
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,820
Principals were Zuo Long and Ma Zhongwu.

146
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,580
We were all accessories.

147
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,100
Four people in total.

148
00:10:36,759 --> 00:10:38,159
You're wrong, Lijun.

149
00:10:38,159 --> 00:10:40,759
Three were involved
in the robbery, not four.

150
00:10:40,759 --> 00:10:42,399
There were only three.

151
00:10:42,399 --> 00:10:44,399
This isn't for telling the police.

152
00:10:45,039 --> 00:10:47,039
This is for telling our own people.

153
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:49,139
Saying four is also a signal.

154
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,500
We were four in total.

155
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:53,159
Four people.

156
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:55,080
Remember our ultimate goal?

157
00:10:55,460 --> 00:10:58,899
Got it. Save whoever we can.

158
00:10:59,379 --> 00:11:03,519
If it comes to it, we admit
to being involved in the robbery,

159
00:11:03,820 --> 00:11:06,580
but we never
admit to being the principals.

160
00:11:06,940 --> 00:11:09,080
Exactly, just stick to that.

161
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:12,340
As long as someone out there
is still in the clear,

162
00:11:12,519 --> 00:11:13,840
then we still have chances.

163
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,399
But if that day truly comes,

164
00:11:16,460 --> 00:11:17,840
how things will unfold

165
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:21,000
is impossible for us to fully predict.

166
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:24,139
Lijun, just say the word.
We'll leave if we have to.

167
00:11:24,139 --> 00:11:25,899
Wait, Guangcai.
We have so much money now.

168
00:11:25,899 --> 00:11:26,960
Where can't we go?

169
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,279
We can go abroad, right?

170
00:11:28,659 --> 00:11:31,019
We're ready to go anytime,

171
00:11:31,460 --> 00:11:32,500
but not now.

172
00:11:33,019 --> 00:11:34,139
What is now?

173
00:11:34,779 --> 00:11:37,279
This is the fastest growth period
for Caisheng Group.

174
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:40,840
Opportunity is raining down
on us right now, you know?

175
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:42,019
That's exactly why

176
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:45,080
we're taking the risk
to discuss our strategy here.

177
00:11:46,519 --> 00:11:49,600
We need to multiply our money tenfold,

178
00:11:49,984 --> 00:11:51,779
twentyfold, even more.

179
00:11:51,779 --> 00:11:54,220
Then we disappear
and live a life of luxury forever.

180
00:11:54,580 --> 00:11:55,779
Eliminate any future threats.

181
00:11:56,580 --> 00:11:58,080
If it reaches the "four people",

182
00:11:59,899 --> 00:12:01,539
we might lose some to protect the boss.

183
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:04,399
If we can only save one person,

184
00:12:05,519 --> 00:12:07,500
it has to be Guangcai.

185
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,000
Qin and Xiaoliang need you.

186
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,200
The company needs you more.

187
00:12:10,639 --> 00:12:12,639
If only one can be saved,
it must be you.

188
00:12:20,539 --> 00:12:22,000
Please clear his name soon.

189
00:12:22,139 --> 00:12:24,840
Let him return to Caisheng Group
quickly to restore morale.

190
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:27,159
He is innocent.

191
00:12:28,779 --> 00:12:30,519
He has nothing to do with any of this.

192
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:35,039
Many of the case details
Jiao Lijun confessed to

193
00:12:35,539 --> 00:12:38,639
basically match the physical evidence
our forensics unit kept from the scene.

194
00:12:38,820 --> 00:12:41,259
Jiao Lijun and Wang Dazhu
both firmly insist

195
00:12:41,259 --> 00:12:44,159
that Zuo Long was the mastermind
and the one who shot.

196
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:47,320
After they overheard
Zuo Long's robbery plan by mistake,

197
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,720
they were forced to be accessories.

198
00:12:49,259 --> 00:12:51,940
After the robbery,
Zuo Long destroyed all the clothing

199
00:12:52,460 --> 00:12:53,519
and took the stolen money.

200
00:12:54,159 --> 00:12:57,700
What's the situation
with the existing evidence and clues?

201
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:01,600
Zuo Long, Ma Zhongwu,
Jiao Lijun, and Wang Dazhu.

202
00:13:01,659 --> 00:13:04,200
The possibility of four co-perpetrators
in the 6.10 case exists.

203
00:13:06,100 --> 00:13:08,600
Meng Guangcai is still
adamantly claiming ignorance?

204
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:09,200
Yes.

205
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:12,700
Meng Guangcai firmly insists
he was not involved in the robbery.

206
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:15,899
He also stated he had no knowledge of
Jiao Lijun's involvement in the robbery.

207
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:20,539
So, we still can't pinpoint
Meng Guangcai as a suspect.

208
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,379
A big shot like Jiao Lijun,
with so much power and status,

209
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,500
he must have a strong motive
for turning himself in.

210
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:30,500
For these people, the most important one
has always been Meng Guangcai.

211
00:13:30,639 --> 00:13:33,460
Are you saying they all want
to take the fall for Meng Guangcai?

212
00:13:33,460 --> 00:13:34,639
Isn't that ridiculous?

213
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,460
Anyone could take the fall for him.

214
00:13:36,879 --> 00:13:37,960
Why would he do it himself?

215
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:41,200
When you pointed out
Wang Dazhu in front of Jiao Lijun,

216
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,659
his reaction was very off.

217
00:13:42,879 --> 00:13:44,600
How was it off?

218
00:13:44,820 --> 00:13:46,460
Wasn't he forced to confess?

219
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:47,519
He was testing you.

220
00:13:47,519 --> 00:13:49,700
These people must have
a meticulous plan.

221
00:13:49,779 --> 00:13:51,080
About Jiao Lijun's surrendering,

222
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,379
beyond taking the blame,

223
00:13:52,899 --> 00:13:55,820
there must be some critical information
we haven't uncovered.

224
00:13:57,960 --> 00:14:00,899
Chief Liu, given this case is so old,

225
00:14:01,659 --> 00:14:03,759
I hope the station
can provide more support.

226
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:06,320
At least let partner units
assist with the investigation.

227
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:08,320
We need to locate this Zuo Long quickly.

228
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:10,100
Zuo Long definitely isn't the principal.

229
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:11,320
He's just a decoy.

230
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,519
Our top priority right now

231
00:14:12,519 --> 00:14:15,100
must still be focusing our efforts
on Meng Guangcai.

232
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:19,320
Zhu, don't let your emotions
cloud your judgment.

233
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:22,879
Handling cases requires evidence.

234
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:25,200
We can't solve cases
on speculation alone.

235
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,080
Fine, let's just say

236
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:32,200
Meng Guangcai wasn't directly
involved in the robbery.

237
00:14:32,288 --> 00:14:35,940
But with his years of friendship
with Jiao Lijun and Wang Dazhu,

238
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:37,960
could he really not know?

239
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,320
Even if not directly involved,

240
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:42,700
if he planned, organized,
or instigated, he's still guilty.

241
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:48,659
Comrades, in a significant case,
relying solely on inference won't do.

242
00:14:48,659 --> 00:14:50,379
This way, we'll make mistakes.

243
00:14:50,379 --> 00:14:52,940
Not we. Me. It's me, Zhu Helai.

244
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:55,379
I made the mistake. It's my fault.

245
00:14:55,379 --> 00:14:58,320
I know the 6.10 case is a hot potato

246
00:14:58,899 --> 00:15:00,840
for the station,
the task force, and for you.

247
00:15:01,039 --> 00:15:02,460
You've been wanting to bench me.

248
00:15:02,460 --> 00:15:03,879
You just haven't said it, right?

249
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,500
Captain Li, come here.

250
00:15:07,539 --> 00:15:08,100
Yes.

251
00:15:12,485 --> 00:15:17,509
(2000, Beiyan Police Station)

252
00:15:20,519 --> 00:15:21,879
- Li.
- Here!

253
00:15:22,379 --> 00:15:24,759
Step out for a moment.
I need to speak with Officer Zhu.

254
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:29,320
Close the door.

255
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:40,379
Zhu Helai.

256
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:43,259
Aren't we partners on the 6.10 case?

257
00:15:44,460 --> 00:15:45,759
Why are you cutting me out?

258
00:15:48,259 --> 00:15:51,200
This is a rare opportunity for you.

259
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,600
Seize it, and you'll move up.

260
00:15:53,039 --> 00:15:54,759
Don't let this case hold you back.

261
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:58,580
You take all the blame yourself,

262
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:00,960
and leave me completely out of it.

263
00:16:01,019 --> 00:16:03,519
Zhu Helai, do you think
you're really something?

264
00:16:03,759 --> 00:16:05,460
What kind of person do you think I am?

265
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:06,700
Laoer, listen.

266
00:16:07,379 --> 00:16:09,519
You're definitely meant
for bigger things.

267
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:11,460
Besides, Laosan ended up in that state,

268
00:16:11,460 --> 00:16:13,139
because he was helping me
withdraw money.

269
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:15,159
I'm sticking with this case to the end.

270
00:16:16,019 --> 00:16:16,899
Seven years.

271
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:18,500
Zhu.

272
00:16:19,180 --> 00:16:20,940
Seven years!
How many times do I have to say?

273
00:16:21,539 --> 00:16:22,500
Laoer, listen.

274
00:16:23,159 --> 00:16:25,879
We can't both
keep wasting our time on this.

275
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:28,600
And if you become a chief,

276
00:16:28,759 --> 00:16:31,320
that will help us
crack the 6.10 case, right?

277
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,399
The 6.10 case hasn't had any new leads.

278
00:16:38,940 --> 00:16:40,399
Diving into this cold case alone

279
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,320
is just a waste of time.

280
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:44,879
I wouldn't say there are no new leads.

281
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:46,320
It's getting close.

282
00:16:47,220 --> 00:16:48,720
As long as these guys aren't gods,

283
00:16:49,379 --> 00:16:51,100
they must have left traces.

284
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,000
The net is tightening. It's close.

285
00:16:55,960 --> 00:16:57,100
Tell me the truth.

286
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,139
You suspect Meng Guangcai, don't you?

287
00:17:03,019 --> 00:17:05,940
Listen, he is no small player now.

288
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:10,599
I found out Xie Kaiyan from Beiyan Bank
approved a loan for him.

289
00:17:11,599 --> 00:17:12,960
He bought out all the stalls.

290
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:16,559
Now the entire Baima Market
answers to Meng Guangcai.

291
00:17:25,312 --> 00:17:27,680
Wow, it smells good.

292
00:17:32,559 --> 00:17:35,920
We earned it all legitimately.

293
00:17:36,519 --> 00:17:37,500
A full five million.

294
00:17:39,299 --> 00:17:40,720
It smells wonderful.

295
00:17:41,559 --> 00:17:43,000
That's the smell.

296
00:17:43,420 --> 00:17:44,680
That's the smell!

297
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,952
Guangcai, if I'd known
it would be like this,

298
00:17:49,952 --> 00:17:51,599
why did we come here today?

299
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:53,640
I can book a nice hotel.

300
00:17:55,259 --> 00:17:58,848
With your wallet full,
you talk differently now.

301
00:17:59,799 --> 00:18:02,960
I remember we stayed here back then
because we were collecting a debt.

302
00:18:03,420 --> 00:18:04,680
What did you say back then?

303
00:18:05,180 --> 00:18:06,579
Yes, right here.

304
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:08,579
This is where you said it.

305
00:18:08,579 --> 00:18:11,920
You said, "I want
to live here every day!"

306
00:18:12,059 --> 00:18:13,200
That was you, wasn't it?

307
00:18:15,559 --> 00:18:17,259
Back then, this place felt like heaven.

308
00:18:17,259 --> 00:18:18,460
Even the carpet amazed me.

309
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:21,079
Now, looking at it again,
it's nothing special.

310
00:18:23,339 --> 00:18:24,420
The hotel hasn't changed.

311
00:18:27,099 --> 00:18:28,200
We have.

312
00:18:33,099 --> 00:18:34,519
I remember that day.

313
00:18:35,420 --> 00:18:36,500
What was it I said?

314
00:18:37,099 --> 00:18:40,299
Why can't we become city folk?

315
00:18:40,579 --> 00:18:41,420
What about now?

316
00:18:43,579 --> 00:18:45,920
Times are different now.

317
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:48,940
We are

318
00:18:50,319 --> 00:18:51,460
finally back.

319
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,819
I will make this business big.

320
00:18:54,220 --> 00:18:56,920
Beiyan's transitioning
from county to city now.

321
00:18:57,319 --> 00:18:58,799
Baima Market's getting renovated.

322
00:18:59,339 --> 00:19:02,799
All those buildings will be sprouting up
from the ground to the sky.

323
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,839
Heaven's on our side.

324
00:19:07,099 --> 00:19:10,680
We will definitely become bosses
in the skyscrapers we build ourselves.

325
00:19:11,319 --> 00:19:14,559
To live lives even city folk
wouldn't dare dream of.

326
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:34,819
Stand up straight, Qianqian.

327
00:19:34,819 --> 00:19:35,799
(2001, Beiyan City, Zhu Helai's Home)

328
00:19:35,799 --> 00:19:36,819
Straighten up.

329
00:19:37,180 --> 00:19:38,079
No tiptoeing.

330
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,220
Let me see.

331
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:42,500
How tall are you?

332
00:19:43,579 --> 00:19:44,960
You've grown taller again!

333
00:19:45,599 --> 00:19:47,819
Look at you. It hasn't been that long.

334
00:19:48,319 --> 00:19:49,579
Mom's back.

335
00:19:49,579 --> 00:19:50,339
You're back.

336
00:19:50,339 --> 00:19:52,619
I was worried you might not
have an umbrella for the rain.

337
00:20:00,940 --> 00:20:03,579
Dad, Mom doesn't seem happy.

338
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:06,079
No, she is just a bit tired.

339
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,880
Qianqian, come on.
Let's go review your homework.

340
00:20:10,799 --> 00:20:11,819
Study hard.

341
00:20:12,420 --> 00:20:13,579
I will check it later.

342
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:16,200
Read your book.

343
00:20:23,920 --> 00:20:24,700
Have some water.

344
00:20:26,019 --> 00:20:27,940
You must be tired. Have some water.

345
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:38,559
The factory only paid half the salary
again this month.

346
00:20:39,579 --> 00:20:41,059
Now Qianqian's grown up.

347
00:20:41,559 --> 00:20:43,720
Money's needed everywhere.
Everything's so expensive.

348
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:46,799
I'm useless.

349
00:20:47,579 --> 00:20:50,440
No, that's not what I meant.

350
00:20:51,579 --> 00:20:52,640
I was just thinking

351
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:56,140
maybe I should find a different job.

352
00:20:57,460 --> 00:20:59,940
No, you'd be too tired.

353
00:21:01,319 --> 00:21:02,640
Don't be so absolute.

354
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:05,640
Well, you find around for me,

355
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:06,960
and I'll find too.

356
00:21:07,819 --> 00:21:09,720
See if there's any suitable work.

357
00:21:14,799 --> 00:21:16,299
Okay. Don't worry about it.

358
00:21:17,579 --> 00:21:18,460
Rest for a bit.

359
00:21:19,059 --> 00:21:20,559
I'll make you something good to eat.

360
00:21:27,819 --> 00:21:28,599
Officer Zhu.

361
00:21:30,016 --> 00:21:31,180
From the district station?

362
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:32,140
Yes.

363
00:21:32,460 --> 00:21:35,420
In college, I majored in Police Command,
and criminal investigation.

364
00:21:35,420 --> 00:21:36,799
The chief sent me to learn.

365
00:21:37,420 --> 00:21:39,140
Here. This is my file.

366
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:42,019
Alright, go change into plain clothes.

367
00:21:42,559 --> 00:21:43,339
We're going out.

368
00:21:52,799 --> 00:21:54,720
Officer Zhu, where are we
heading for the case?

369
00:21:55,059 --> 00:21:56,140
Why aren't we taking a car?

370
00:21:56,832 --> 00:21:58,112
Not enough cars at the station.

371
00:21:58,559 --> 00:22:00,720
And I've been working this case
for too long.

372
00:22:02,819 --> 00:22:03,799
Feel wronged?

373
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:05,460
No. Not at all.

374
00:22:06,319 --> 00:22:09,079
If you're done working with me,
tell me in advance.

375
00:22:09,319 --> 00:22:10,720
I'll report it up the chain.

376
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,640
No! Officer Zhu! That's not it!

377
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:16,220
Zhang Wei, since you're with me now,

378
00:22:16,579 --> 00:22:19,559
don't call me Officer Zhu anymore.
Call me Master.

379
00:22:20,140 --> 00:22:20,960
Yes, Master.

380
00:22:27,488 --> 00:22:34,488
(Xiyuan Complex North Gate,
North City Bus Terminal)

381
00:22:43,460 --> 00:22:45,380
We were fighting over
who'd pay the bill.

382
00:22:46,319 --> 00:22:47,599
Then the watch case fell off.

383
00:22:48,319 --> 00:22:49,940
I said, "Bro, this is a fake, right?"

384
00:22:50,299 --> 00:22:51,200
He said, "It's real."

385
00:22:51,299 --> 00:22:52,799
So I said, "If it's real, you pay."

386
00:22:53,380 --> 00:22:54,259
He went silent.

387
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:56,079
What kind of person is that?

388
00:22:57,940 --> 00:22:59,559
Sorry about this, bro.

389
00:23:08,259 --> 00:23:10,380
I saw a childhood neighbor.
I'll go say hi.

390
00:23:10,579 --> 00:23:11,140
Okay.

391
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:16,140
Excuse me, bro. Let me through. Come on.

392
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,559
So many years have passed in a flash.

393
00:23:30,599 --> 00:23:32,400
Never thought we'd meet on the bus.

394
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:33,880
What a coincidence.

395
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:35,579
You've lost weight.

396
00:23:36,579 --> 00:23:39,180
You're a rich boss now.
Why don't you get yourself a car?

397
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:40,640
Me?

398
00:23:43,299 --> 00:23:44,319
I'm thinking about it.

399
00:23:45,799 --> 00:23:47,559
I'm doing odd brokerage gigs now.

400
00:23:47,940 --> 00:23:49,299
One deal here, nothing there.

401
00:23:49,299 --> 00:23:50,680
Just save where I can.

402
00:23:52,960 --> 00:23:54,180
You were doing well.

403
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:56,640
The unit trained you for years.

404
00:23:56,999 --> 00:23:57,799
And you just leave?

405
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:02,579
Am I not living well now?

406
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:05,000
Life is life, however you live it.

407
00:24:09,799 --> 00:24:10,640
Girlfriend?

408
00:24:12,319 --> 00:24:13,140
How is she?

409
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:19,460
A female friend,
not exactly a girlfriend.

410
00:24:19,460 --> 00:24:21,460
How's life now
that you're not a cop anymore?

411
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:22,440
Are you okay?

412
00:24:26,559 --> 00:24:27,680
Not bad.

413
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:29,440
Pretty good.

414
00:24:31,079 --> 00:24:32,019
Oh, right.

415
00:24:35,579 --> 00:24:36,700
Here. Take this money.

416
00:24:36,940 --> 00:24:38,976
No.

417
00:24:38,976 --> 00:24:40,032
Listen! Stop the fussing.

418
00:24:40,032 --> 00:24:41,200
- No!
- Just take it!

419
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,460
This money is for Qianqian.

420
00:24:42,460 --> 00:24:43,799
She's growing up and needs money.

421
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:44,799
I have enough.

422
00:24:45,299 --> 00:24:46,460
- Take it!
- I have enough!

423
00:24:50,940 --> 00:24:51,599
Alright.

424
00:24:55,579 --> 00:24:57,500
I just saw my old friend.

425
00:24:59,319 --> 00:25:00,460
Goodbye, my buddy!

426
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:10,940
Master, who is he?

427
00:25:13,579 --> 00:25:14,559
A friend.

428
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:25,700
Dad!

429
00:25:26,319 --> 00:25:26,819
Come here.

430
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:27,819
Be careful.

431
00:25:28,519 --> 00:25:29,640
Slow down.

432
00:25:33,559 --> 00:25:34,460
Sit properly.

433
00:26:07,299 --> 00:26:08,559
Good!

434
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:29,299
Good!

435
00:26:29,819 --> 00:26:30,464
Good!

436
00:26:31,180 --> 00:26:31,680
Come here.

437
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:32,799
Come here, Xiaoliang.

438
00:26:37,319 --> 00:26:39,079
Isn't the new house
I built for Grandpa nice?

439
00:26:40,960 --> 00:26:41,960
Mom likes it too.

440
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,680
Ma'am, it's almost ready.

441
00:26:51,799 --> 00:26:53,380
Come inside! Please.

442
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:54,460
Please! Just come in!

443
00:26:54,460 --> 00:26:56,460
- After the reinforcements arrived,
- Guangcai!

444
00:26:56,460 --> 00:26:58,079
- it took the food back home.
- Guangcai!

445
00:26:58,640 --> 00:27:01,920
Look, Officer Zhu sent a gift
before he even arrived.

446
00:27:02,420 --> 00:27:03,519
And this is from me.

447
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:05,720
Give this to your Zhu.

448
00:27:06,140 --> 00:27:07,579
Tell him to come by when he's free.

449
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:09,559
Okay.

450
00:27:10,700 --> 00:27:12,799
Alright, you guys
go ahead. I'll head over.

451
00:27:12,799 --> 00:27:13,504
Okay.

452
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:20,640
It's fine.

453
00:27:26,940 --> 00:27:28,259
You told Zhu too?

454
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:33,420
Anyway, he's helped us a lot
over the years.

455
00:27:33,539 --> 00:27:36,700
On such a happy day,
we should have told him.

456
00:27:52,420 --> 00:27:53,200
What's going on?

457
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:54,940
Look at what they did to us!

458
00:27:55,079 --> 00:27:57,420
They must be sent by Caisheng Group.

459
00:27:57,420 --> 00:27:59,420
They feared we'd ask
for more demolition pay.

460
00:27:59,599 --> 00:28:01,319
- Look what you did to us!
- Nonsense. What are you saying?

461
00:28:01,319 --> 00:28:02,460
- What are you doing?
- Behave!

462
00:28:02,460 --> 00:28:03,579
- Go back!
- Step back!

463
00:28:03,579 --> 00:28:05,319
Officer, the statement is done.

464
00:28:05,319 --> 00:28:06,299
Can we go now?

465
00:28:06,460 --> 00:28:07,079
Stand properly!

466
00:28:09,420 --> 00:28:10,299
- Officer Zhu!
- Officer Zhu!

467
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:13,700
Liu Hua, I just questioned
those injured guys at the entrance.

468
00:28:13,819 --> 00:28:15,299
It must be Caisheng Group.

469
00:28:15,460 --> 00:28:16,920
Have their statements been sent?

470
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:19,079
Are these them?

471
00:28:20,749 --> 00:28:22,279
Could you touch anything on that desk?

472
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:24,299
And don't waste time here.

473
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:27,299
Listen. That matter
has nothing to do with this.

474
00:28:28,380 --> 00:28:29,680
Someone's on it. Stay out of it.

475
00:28:29,880 --> 00:28:31,299
No, you promised me.

476
00:28:31,420 --> 00:28:32,200
Now you're chief.

477
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:34,960
You'll support me
on Caisheng Group matters.

478
00:28:35,420 --> 00:28:35,960
Give...

479
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:37,079
- Who're you cursing?
- Give me.

480
00:28:37,079 --> 00:28:37,920
We four are buddies.

481
00:28:37,920 --> 00:28:40,200
When it's just us, we're buddies.
No chiefs here.

482
00:28:41,299 --> 00:28:43,420
You said it yourself.
No chiefs right now.

483
00:28:43,759 --> 00:28:44,559
You're just Laoer.

484
00:28:44,559 --> 00:28:45,799
I'm Laoda. Obey me.

485
00:28:45,799 --> 00:28:46,799
Give me the files.

486
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,319
Liu Hua, the key.

487
00:28:52,559 --> 00:28:53,380
No key.

488
00:28:53,819 --> 00:28:55,799
I find you are so stubborn!

489
00:28:56,579 --> 00:28:58,920
T-This is just an ordinary dispute.

490
00:28:58,920 --> 00:29:00,559
It has nothing to do
with Caisheng Group.

491
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:01,799
I just asked.

492
00:29:02,380 --> 00:29:05,000
They didn't settle with Caisheng Group
on the demolition pay.

493
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:06,420
On the way back, they got stopped.

494
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:08,960
Those guys are
definitely suspects. Trust me.

495
00:29:09,299 --> 00:29:10,000
Give me the key.

496
00:29:10,319 --> 00:29:11,819
Zhu Helai, you're so stubborn.

497
00:29:12,339 --> 00:29:15,420
Can you stop tying everything
to Caisheng Group?

498
00:29:16,099 --> 00:29:16,819
Give it or not?

499
00:29:17,579 --> 00:29:18,339
No.

500
00:29:20,079 --> 00:29:22,559
Then forget about keeping
your precious tea too.

501
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:25,819
Why did you take my tea?

502
00:29:29,140 --> 00:29:30,259
Four times six.

503
00:29:31,059 --> 00:29:32,220
Twenty-four.

504
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:33,720
Four times seven.

505
00:29:33,960 --> 00:29:35,180
Twenty-eight.

506
00:29:35,319 --> 00:29:36,420
Four times nine.

507
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:37,920
Thirty-six.

508
00:29:38,500 --> 00:29:39,319
Nine times seven.

509
00:29:40,500 --> 00:29:41,380
Sixty-three.

510
00:29:41,799 --> 00:29:43,460
Nice! Didn't stump you.

511
00:29:46,299 --> 00:29:47,299
Dad.

512
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:50,059
Your dad's not home. He's always busy.

513
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:54,700
Let me see.

514
00:29:56,299 --> 00:29:59,079
I'm going out for a walk.

515
00:29:59,079 --> 00:30:00,039
For a bit.

516
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:01,180
For a bit.

517
00:30:01,440 --> 00:30:04,319
You two eat first.

518
00:30:04,579 --> 00:30:08,599
When you're done, wait for me
to come back and wash...

519
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:09,680
Dishes.

520
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:10,940
Wash the dishes.

521
00:30:11,799 --> 00:30:12,799
I want to eat.

522
00:30:13,079 --> 00:30:15,220
Wait! Put it down. Go wash your hands.

523
00:30:16,559 --> 00:30:17,460
This spring morning...

524
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:18,599
In bed I'm lying.

525
00:30:18,599 --> 00:30:19,500
Not to awake...

526
00:30:19,500 --> 00:30:20,579
Till birds are crying.

527
00:30:31,140 --> 00:30:32,539
Madam, can we get more hot water?

528
00:30:40,299 --> 00:30:41,640
Here. Let me add some for you.

529
00:30:42,220 --> 00:30:43,000
Thank you.

530
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:44,940
Would you like anything else?

531
00:30:45,380 --> 00:30:46,700
No, this is enough.

532
00:30:46,700 --> 00:30:49,339
I saw you sitting here.
Are you waiting for someone?

533
00:30:49,819 --> 00:30:51,960
Your child works here, right?

534
00:30:59,059 --> 00:30:59,720
Madam.

535
00:31:01,059 --> 00:31:03,559
You've had this stall here
for quite a while now, haven't you?

536
00:31:04,819 --> 00:31:07,380
Won't be here much longer.
They're tearing it down soon.

537
00:31:07,700 --> 00:31:11,960
All these buildings ahead
are coming down. Everyone's got to move.

538
00:31:12,420 --> 00:31:15,700
If they're getting torn down,
they'll get a lot of money, right?

539
00:31:16,700 --> 00:31:19,380
How would we know?
We're just running a small business.

540
00:31:19,660 --> 00:31:23,559
But I've heard Caisheng Group
is really wealthy.

541
00:31:23,779 --> 00:31:26,680
They're in charge of
demolishing this whole area.

542
00:31:27,019 --> 00:31:30,720
I heard they're going
to build Beiyan's biggest market.

543
00:31:31,059 --> 00:31:32,039
And housing.

544
00:31:46,099 --> 00:31:47,660
Madam, how much is this?

545
00:31:48,039 --> 00:31:48,640
Six yuan.

546
00:31:48,799 --> 00:31:49,779
Okay, money's here.

547
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:50,519
Got it.

548
00:31:51,392 --> 00:31:56,512
(Caisheng Group)

549
00:32:03,039 --> 00:32:03,920
Wang Dazhu.

550
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:07,200
Officer Zhu, long time no see.

551
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:07,920
- Get out.
- I'm busy.

552
00:32:08,259 --> 00:32:09,339
I'll go in first.

553
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:11,779
Wang Dazhu!

554
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:20,140
Officer Zhu.

555
00:32:20,140 --> 00:32:22,299
How dangerous! What are you doing?

556
00:32:24,440 --> 00:32:26,180
Where's Meng Guangcai?
Need to talk to him.

557
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:28,660
Guangcai went out of town.

558
00:32:28,660 --> 00:32:29,759
Any problem?

559
00:32:31,299 --> 00:32:32,339
Then you'll do.

560
00:32:33,539 --> 00:32:35,160
A couple of days ago, your people

561
00:32:36,019 --> 00:32:38,099
had a run-in with residents
facing demolition.

562
00:32:38,559 --> 00:32:39,920
Almost came to blows, didn't it?

563
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:41,920
I'm here to find out.

564
00:32:43,299 --> 00:32:46,380
Is that so? I didn't hear about it.

565
00:32:51,519 --> 00:32:52,339
I'll ask others.

566
00:32:53,900 --> 00:32:57,140
Officer Zhu, look.
It's really dangerous inside.

567
00:32:57,140 --> 00:32:57,920
Under construction.

568
00:32:58,019 --> 00:33:00,940
You don't even have a hard hat.

569
00:33:01,180 --> 00:33:05,019
What if you get hit
or injured? What then?

570
00:33:05,779 --> 00:33:08,180
Who's going to take the blame then?

571
00:33:10,099 --> 00:33:13,420
This project has been
under construction for a while, right?

572
00:33:14,660 --> 00:33:18,880
All the construction permits
have been approved.

573
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:22,140
You can rest assured about that.
No issues whatsoever.

574
00:33:23,019 --> 00:33:23,920
How about this?

575
00:33:24,059 --> 00:33:27,299
Officer Zhu, why don't you
head back first?

576
00:33:27,299 --> 00:33:29,920
Once Guangcai gets back,

577
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:32,660
I'll report this to him immediately.

578
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:34,099
We'll invite you over again.

579
00:33:34,420 --> 00:33:36,019
That should be fine, right?

580
00:33:37,799 --> 00:33:41,720
Someone! Come on!
Ensure Officer Zhu's safety!

581
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:43,160
- Safety first!
- Sorry.

582
00:33:43,680 --> 00:33:45,160
Sorry, could you please step out?

583
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:46,539
Sorry, please step out.

584
00:33:47,230 --> 00:33:47,880
Please step out.

585
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:48,680
Sorry, officer.

586
00:33:48,779 --> 00:33:49,660
Please step out.

587
00:33:50,779 --> 00:33:53,039
Sorry, our boss said no one can go in.

588
00:33:53,099 --> 00:33:53,880
Please step out.

589
00:33:56,420 --> 00:33:57,180
Please step out.

590
00:33:58,640 --> 00:33:59,400
Please step out.

591
00:34:00,079 --> 00:34:01,440
Sorry.

592
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:04,660
Sorry.

593
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:14,539
Guangcai.

594
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:19,719
Officer Zhu just stopped me at the gate.

595
00:34:20,059 --> 00:34:22,139
He wanted to ask about the demolition.

596
00:34:32,539 --> 00:34:34,900
Why is Zhu so hard to shake off?

597
00:34:36,059 --> 00:34:38,400
Didn't we come here today
specifically to deal with this?

598
00:34:40,019 --> 00:34:41,300
I already sent him away.

599
00:34:41,300 --> 00:34:44,900
But I see he's still over there.
He hasn't gone far.

600
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:47,179
If he wants to wait, let him wait.

601
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:51,300
Listen. In a bit, you move the car.

602
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:54,280
Go out the back gate.
Take the bosses back.

603
00:34:55,019 --> 00:34:56,539
Xie Kaiyan will stay here.

604
00:34:56,619 --> 00:34:57,559
Lijun drank too much.

605
00:34:57,900 --> 00:34:59,519
You arrange the evening activities.

606
00:34:59,619 --> 00:35:00,639
Okay, I understand.

607
00:35:05,780 --> 00:35:07,139
Come on.

608
00:35:07,139 --> 00:35:07,760
Come on.

609
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:08,820
Come on! Let's drink!

610
00:35:08,820 --> 00:35:10,440
Everyone, let's jump.

611
00:35:10,699 --> 00:35:11,800
Let's dance.

612
00:35:17,039 --> 00:35:18,840
Come on! Let's shake!

613
00:35:21,039 --> 00:35:22,619
Come on.

614
00:35:31,119 --> 00:35:36,320
It's just a dead guy.
What more do you want me to say?

615
00:35:36,960 --> 00:35:38,960
You don't get to call that.

616
00:35:39,059 --> 00:35:40,119
Cooperate properly.

617
00:35:40,639 --> 00:35:41,139
Fine.

618
00:35:42,199 --> 00:35:44,199
Then I'll say it again.

619
00:35:44,300 --> 00:35:47,380
He used to be
from the same village as us.

620
00:35:48,119 --> 00:35:50,300
Later, he ran away. Then he came back.

621
00:35:50,300 --> 00:35:51,699
He had a terminal illness. Died.

622
00:35:51,699 --> 00:35:52,699
That's all.

623
00:35:53,639 --> 00:35:55,760
Be more specific.
When did he leave Beiyan?

624
00:35:55,900 --> 00:35:56,699
I don't know.

625
00:35:57,699 --> 00:36:01,320
So, to your knowledge,
after Huang Mantang returned to Beiyan,

626
00:36:01,860 --> 00:36:03,800
did any relatives or friends see him?

627
00:36:04,199 --> 00:36:05,340
I don't know.

628
00:36:05,699 --> 00:36:07,500
There's no way you don't know something.

629
00:36:08,659 --> 00:36:11,260
Okay, officers, how about this?

630
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:16,159
I'll make up a story for you
right now. How about that?

631
00:36:18,960 --> 00:36:23,780
(Mr. Xue Yonghui is an outstanding
young entrepreneur with a disability.)

632
00:36:24,199 --> 00:36:28,219
(Ten years ago, he founded
Yonghui Textile Co., Ltd.)

633
00:36:28,519 --> 00:36:30,699
(This is a welfare-oriented enterprise.)

634
00:36:31,260 --> 00:36:35,360
(It's touching that despite
having a disabled left arm,)

635
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:38,460
(he didn't get discouraged
but persisted in building his career)

636
00:36:38,460 --> 00:36:39,620
(and giving back to society.)

637
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:42,199
(For many years, Mr. Xue Yonghui...)

638
00:36:56,780 --> 00:36:57,880
Who is it?

639
00:37:01,760 --> 00:37:02,960
Stop knocking!

640
00:37:06,059 --> 00:37:07,960
Babe!

641
00:37:09,260 --> 00:37:11,440
Did you miss me?

642
00:37:17,199 --> 00:37:17,880
Go away.

643
00:37:20,559 --> 00:37:22,119
Why are you here again?

644
00:37:22,119 --> 00:37:25,320
Isn't your boss watching you
all the time?

645
00:37:26,119 --> 00:37:28,199
What kind of lousy boss is that?

646
00:37:28,659 --> 00:37:30,760
In my eyes, he's just a fart.

647
00:37:32,260 --> 00:37:33,940
I'd just blow him away.

648
00:37:34,780 --> 00:37:36,659
Getting bold, huh?

649
00:37:42,500 --> 00:37:44,199
Babe, how about it?

650
00:37:44,659 --> 00:37:46,659
Want to play something wild today?

651
00:37:47,440 --> 00:37:49,059
Who wants to play with you?

652
00:37:50,579 --> 00:37:51,719
Come on.

653
00:37:53,179 --> 00:37:53,940
Babe.

654
00:37:55,159 --> 00:37:56,460
What's your rush?

655
00:37:56,719 --> 00:37:58,019
- What's your rush?
- No rush...

656
00:38:00,760 --> 00:38:02,960
- Did you arrange to meet someone else?
- No, I didn't.

657
00:38:04,119 --> 00:38:05,860
Who's knocking? Get lost!

658
00:38:17,159 --> 00:38:20,659
M-Mr. Yonghui.

659
00:38:21,300 --> 00:38:22,340
I'll go, Mr. Yonghui.

660
00:38:23,699 --> 00:38:24,219
Let me go.

661
00:38:26,860 --> 00:38:28,019
Well, are you insane?

662
00:38:28,019 --> 00:38:29,699
Couldn't you have come
half an hour later?

663
00:38:31,900 --> 00:38:33,800
Mr. Yonghui, I just
came out for some air.

664
00:38:41,119 --> 00:38:42,900
Mr. Yonghui!

665
00:38:44,199 --> 00:38:45,420
Don't kick me, Mr. Yonghui!

666
00:38:46,420 --> 00:38:47,199
Mr. Yonghui!

667
00:38:52,219 --> 00:38:55,000
Mr. Yonghui! Stop hitting me!

668
00:39:00,900 --> 00:39:02,780
Didn't I tell you not to run off?

669
00:39:03,659 --> 00:39:04,400
Yes, you did.

670
00:39:07,199 --> 00:39:08,360
Answer me, Chai Daqing.

671
00:39:10,699 --> 00:39:12,260
Don't call me Chai Daqing.

672
00:39:14,300 --> 00:39:19,320
Why do you get to strut around
like big shots in this world?

673
00:39:19,699 --> 00:39:23,659
You found a fall guy
to bury in that pit for me.

674
00:39:24,900 --> 00:39:27,400
I'm telling you, I don't acknowledge it.

675
00:39:28,119 --> 00:39:29,500
I'm not dead.

676
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,760
My name is Huang Mantang.

677
00:39:35,980 --> 00:39:41,004
=The Silent Rift=
